[1] China - MOH SARS update
Date: 25 Apr 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: China - MOH [machine trans. edited]
<http://www.moh.gov.cn/zhgl/zt/yqfb/1200404250003.htm>

From the Medical Department Public News Office: 25 Apr 2004 SARS update
----------------------
During the period 10 AM 24 Apr 2004 through 10 AM 25 Apr 2004, Beijing
reported 4 suspected cases of SARS. There were no reports of additional
cases from other provinces.
The 4 suspected cases reported by Beijing include contacts of [the nurse
who had cared for the index patient from Anhui]. Her father has a fever
without signs of pneumonia, her mother has fever with signs of worsening
pneumonia, her aunt with a fever and no signs of pneumonia, and a patient
from the ward [?from same room as either the nurse or the index patient]
with a fever and no signs of pneumonia.
At present there are 337 close contacts of the patients in Beijing that are
under observation, and 133 close contacts of the patient in Anhui [the
index case] who are under observation.
Since 22 Apr 2004, there has been one case of SARS confirmed in Anhui and
one suspected case of SARS from Anhui. There has been one case of SARS
confirmed in Beijing and 4 suspected cases of SARS reported from
Beijing. There have been no additional confirmed or suspected cases from
other provinces.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
