[2] China - MOH / Anhui Province announcement
Date: 25 Apr 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: China MOH / Anhui Province Health Dept. announcement [machine
transl.; edited]
<http://www.moh.gov.cn/zhgl/zt/fdgzdt/1200404250002.htm>

On 23 Apr 2004, our Province [Anhui] has diagnosed 2 patients with SARS
with a history of train travel to the province.
On 6 Mar 2004, there was travel on the Hefei - Beijing line 1410 train
On 23 Mar 2004, there was travel on the Beijing - Hefei T63 "inferior"
train [?second class]
On 27 Mar 2004, there was travel on the Hefei - Beijing T64 "inferior"
train of 17 compartments [?second class]
On 2 Apr 2004 there was travel on the Beijing - Huai Nan 1409 train of 13
compartments
All passengers who were riding on the above-mentioned coaches and
compartments: please report to your local disease control office for
medical evaluation/consultation.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
